## Proposed Changes

### Conventions (apply to ALL features)

Every new feature follows the existing project conventions exactly:

- **Domain**: Entity (Equatable), repository interface (abstract class), pure domain logic — no Flutter imports
- **Application**: Use case classes — single `call()` method, injected via constructor
- **Data**: Supabase implementation of repository interface + Hive offline DAO where needed
- **Presentation**: `bloc/` (sealed events, Equatable states, `Bloc` not `Cubit`), `view/` (pages), `widgets/` (extracted composable widgets)
- **DI**: Wire in `app_providers.dart` via `RepositoryProvider`
- **Routing**: Register in `app_router.dart` with `GoRoute` + Bloc providers
- **UI**: Use existing M3 design system (`AppSpacing`, `AppRadii`, `AppTheme`, `AppMetricCard`, `AppSectionCard`, `AppScreenScaffold`, `AppStatusChip`), Poppins font, `surfaceContainerLow` cards, `colorScheme.primary` accents
- **Performance**: `const` constructors everywhere, `RepaintBoundary` on heavy widgets, `AutomaticKeepAliveClientMixin` on tab contents, `ListView.builder` with `itemExtent` for fixed-height rows, isolate-based computation for lists >500 items

